Goodman is well known in tennis circles 
and was preparing to serve as a referee at the U.S. Open Tennis 
Championships tournament, a district attorney's office spokeswoman, Jane
Robison, said.

She has refereed at the U.S. and Australian Opens for years, according to the Los Angeles Times.

Goodman has umpired with some of the world's top tennis players since the 1970s, including matches featuring Jimmy Connors, John McEnroe and Martina Navratilova.

In a 1994 interview with the L.A. Times, she said: 'It's exciting. This is my favorite sport and I'm out there rubbing shoulders with the best players. There's no real way to describe it.'

